---
title: Bacon, Apple & Cheddar Spinach Salad with Dried Cranberries, Walnuts & Honey Dijon Dressing
description: Step aside, side salad—this hearty spinach version is the stuff of dinner dreams. We toss tender fresh spinach with sweet-tart apple slices, smoky bacon, tangy cheddar, chewy dried cranberries, and a creamy honey Dijon dressing. It’s all topped with crunchy walnuts for a bowlful of delicious textural and flavor contrasts that makes a fresh, light dinner idea you’re going to want to make again and again.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64b69cee8c02aa03441410b9-164137e8.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64b69cee8c02aa03441410b9.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/bacon-apple-and-cheddar-spinach-salad-64b69cee8c02aa03441410b9
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 730 kcal
  fat: 56 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 39 g
  sugar: 28 g
  protein: 18 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 960 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @Granny Smith apple{1}.

Heat a #medium dry nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Using #kitchen shears{}, cut @bacon{4%ounce} into bite-size pieces directly into pan. Cook, stirring occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @spinach{5%ounce}, apple, bacon, half the @white cheddar cheese{½%cup}, half the @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, and half the @walnuts{½%ounce}.

Add as much @honey Dijon dressing{3%ounce} as you like and toss to combine. Season lightly with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide salad between shallow #bowls{}. Top with remaining cheddar, remaining cranberries, and remaining walnuts. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.